OL,4,Cmurder of Danny McClean
OL,6,FA defence lawyer raised objections to
OL,7,Fthe alleged police identification of
OL,8,FBlack on CCTV close to the scene of
OL,9,Fthe O'Reilly shooting.
OL,11,FThe lawyer said there was no DNA,
OL,12,Fballistics or forensic evidence
OL,13,Flinking his client to the incident.
OL,15,FNo details were given in court about
OL,16,Fthe murder of Mr McClean, but the
OL,17,Flawyer said it was a "highly
OL,18,Fcircumstantial case" against his
OL,19,Fclient.
